dcterms:description: This dataset contains technical reports that outline system improvements for machine-type communications, focusing on the challenges and solutions for managing event-driven traffic in massive machine-type communication networks.

dcterms:description: This dataset provides a Beta distribution model for event-driven traffic in machine-type communications, which is used to analyze the traffic patterns and predict congestion.
dcterms:title: Beta Distribution for Event-driven Traffic

dcterms:description: This dataset includes simulation data for massive machine-type communication (mMTC) networks, which is used to evaluate the performance of various algorithms in predicting traffic patterns.
dcterms:title: Simulation Data for mMTC Networks

dcterms:description: This dataset provides configurations for the Random Access Channel (RACH) in mMTC networks, detailing the parameters necessary for managing access requests and preventing congestion.
dcterms:title: RACH Channel Configuration

dcterms:description: This dataset includes information on IoT group sizes and the probability of events triggering traffic in mMTC networks, which is essential for understanding traffic dynamics.
dcterms:title: IoT Group Sizes and Event Probability
